Issue 2: Did the Adjudicator have the jurisdiction to hear and decide the Respondent's complaint?

[48]
Jurisdiction over labour relations is not delegated to either the provincial or federal governments under section 91 or section 92 of the
Constitution Act, 1867
. However, it is well established that "Canadian courts have recognized that labour relations are presumptively a provincial matter, and that the federal government has jurisdiction over labour relations only by way of exception" (
NIL TU,O
at para 11; <FRAGMENT_SUPPRESSED> at para 11;
